# PayGate402 — x402 paywall on Circle Arc Testnet
#
# Quick start:
#   1. npm run generate-wallets   (creates seller + buyer wallets, writes them here)
#   2. Fund the BUYER_ADDRESS with testnet USDC at https://faucet.circle.com (Arc Testnet)
#   3. npm run dev                (seller app on http://localhost:3000)
#   4. npm run agent -- --limit 0.5   (buyer agent pays your endpoints)

# --- Seller (receives USDC). Server-side only. ---
SELLER_ADDRESS=0xYourSellerAddress
# Only needed for the optional Gateway withdraw stretch goal; balance display does not need it.
SELLER_PRIVATE_KEY=0xYourSellerPrivateKey

# --- Buyer funder wallet (the agent spawns ephemeral wallets funded from this one). Fund THIS one. ---
BUYER_ADDRESS=0xYourBuyerAddress
BUYER_PRIVATE_KEY=0xYourBuyerPrivateKey

# --- Optional: real LLM summarization on /api/premium/summarize ---
# Without it, the route falls back to a built-in zero-dependency extractive summarizer.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# --- Optional: where the agent buys from (defaults to http://localhost:3000) ---
# BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# --- ERC-8004 on-chain identity (auto-written by `npm run register-agent`) ---
# AGENT_ID=
# AGENT_ADDRESS=
# Override the agent card URI for a non-local deployment (default: BASE_URL/.well-known/agent-card.json)
# AGENT_METADATA_URI=
